        <p> The journey started on time, nasty waves followed pretty quickly and to distract, there was the snorkeling instruction in extra funny. When this was over, you could already see the first green faces and then it started! We quickly grabbed our headphones, turned Laaaaut up and stared at the sea, so as not to get anything from the others. The waves were extremely angry, but these travacalm are pretty good. I didn't notice anything, only Basti felt a little like in the roller coaster. But he was fine anyway! </p>
		<p> With a stopover on Fitzroy Island, we went to the second stage towards Ponton in the "Moore Reef". The waves felt worse, but when we reached the goal, everything was fine. The pontoon turned out to be very stable in the waves "Jippie" and then everything went very quickly. Basti had to dive immediately and I got to snorkel. Everyone else was still sitting around and trying to calm their stomach. I decided to try it out without a wetsuit or jellyfish and went towards the entry. The lifeguard sabs me an ear "Yeah you are the first, enjoy it" etc. and I clarified the water temperature quote "26 degrees and just the first contact is freeeeesh". Hm ok ... step down, the first leg in the water and fu ... it was fresh. But he was right ... You got used to it immediately. However, I did not have much time to think about it, because unfortunately nobody told me that when you are the first to have the fish with a pagan fun. The silver-yellow fishis are immediately towards me and checked whether there is anything to get. Quite a big crush. </p>
		<p> Packed the feet and let it slide into the water ... Ui Friiiisch and Vieeeeel Fisch. I wasn't even completely under water, because different types of fish sled over, in many different colors below and next to me. The waves were quite annoying, but through the snorkeling vest, it went quite well. So at least I didn't have to concentrate on the top, etc., but was able to enjoy the colorful underwater world. And ... I found Nemo, together with siblings !!! Almost 1 hour later, I urgently needed something to drink and moved towards Ponton. There I met Basti again, who was pretty happy. In addition, a 2nd dive was now in prospect. (a little bit of stinking sometimes helps) </p>
		<p> I briefly told him about my experiences, and that I had found Nemo and he decided to spend his break with me in the water. So back in and Nemo's at home again in the really large snorkeling area searched and found! </p>
