		<p> After Steffi showed me a navestry and the clownfish family, I went to my second dive. This time it should be a cool drift dive. The plan was, my guide and I are stopped with the boat a little away from the pontoon and the current brings us back. Somehow, unfortunately, only nobody expected a counter -current. So we had to swim against the current for 18 minutes, which almost consumed 3/4 of my air stock. Since there was less current on the surface, we decided to snorkel out of the current and to lift the remaining air for the more beautiful part. After another 5 minutes we had found the right flow direction and dived again. Since I only had very little air, I decided to stay at just 2m to consume less. With only 19 bar remaining pressure (approx. 3 to 5 minutes diving time) we arrived again on the pontoon. Was a really exhausting dive, but it was still good. </p>
		<p> A short time later we all went back to the board of the ship and drove back to Cairn. Thanks to Travacalms, we also had no seasickness problems thanks to Travacalm. </p>
